---
import ReportLayout from '@/components/ReportLayout.astro';
---

<ReportLayout title="Competitor Analysis Agent">

  <section class="agent-intro">
    <p class="agent-eyebrow">Agent Guide</p>
    <h1 class="agent-h1">Competitor Analysis</h1>
    <p class="agent-summary">
      The Competitor Analysis agent reviews a competitor's page side-by-side with the equivalent
      Myprotein page, and surfaces only genuine gaps — patterns the competitor does that Myprotein
      doesn't, or doesn't do as well. It's deliberately conservative: zero findings is a valid
      result, and a finding is only included if the agent can show both sides of the comparison with
      a screenshot. Use it when you're starting a redesign and want to know what the market is doing,
      or when a specific competitor is getting attention and you want to understand why.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Setup callout ─────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <a href="/getting-started" class="setup-callout">
    <span class="setup-callout-icon">⚙</span>
    <div>
      <p class="setup-callout-title">First time? Complete the setup guide first</p>
      <p class="setup-callout-sub">You'll need GitHub Desktop, the Claude Code desktop app, the Chrome extension, and the agent skills installed before any agent will work. →</p>
    </div>
  </a>

  <!-- ── Before you start ────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="guide-section">
    <h2 class="section-heading">Before you start</h2>
    <ul class="checklist">
      <li>The full URL of the competitor page you want analysed</li>
      <li>The full URL of the equivalent Myprotein page (e.g. their PDP vs our PDP for a comparable product)</li>
      <li>Both URLs should be publicly accessible — no login required</li>
      <li>Have a clear page type in mind (PDP, PLP, basket, checkout) — the agent compares like-for-like, not across different page types</li>
      <li>You're running Claude Code inside this repo so the agent can commit the output files</li>
      <li>
        <strong>One-time Chrome setup:</strong> in Chrome, go to
        <strong>View → Developer → Allow JavaScript from Apple Events</strong> and make sure it is
        ticked. This lets the agent read page content from Chrome tabs via AppleScript. You only
        need to do this once — Chrome remembers the setting across restarts.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <!-- ── How to trigger ──────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="guide-section">
    <h2 class="section-heading">How to trigger it</h2>
    <p class="guide-body">Use the slash command directly, or describe the comparison in plain English:</p>
    <div class="trigger-block">
      <code class="trigger-command">/competitor-analysis</code>
    </div>
    <div class="trigger-examples">
      <span class="trigger-chip">"compare Gymshark's PDP to ours"</span>
      <span class="trigger-chip">"what does Bulk do well on their basket?"</span>
      <span class="trigger-chip">"look at [competitor URL] and find opportunities"</span>
      <span class="trigger-chip">"anything worth stealing from this page?"</span>
    </div>
    <p class="guide-body guide-body--tip">Include both the competitor URL and the Myprotein URL in your message. If you only provide one URL, the agent will ask for the other before starting.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Step-by-step walkthrough ───────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="guide-section">
    <h2 class="section-heading">Step-by-step walkthrough</h2>
    <ol class="steps">
      <li class="step">
        <span class="step-number">1</span>
        <div class="step-body">
          <h3 class="step-title">URL validation and report slug</h3>
          <p class="step-desc">
            The agent confirms it has both URLs, identifies the page type (PDP, PLP, basket, etc.),
            and derives a report slug from the competitor brand name and page type, e.g.
            <code>pdp-competitor-analysis-2026-06-08</code>. It will confirm the slug with you if it's
            uncertain.
          </p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="step">
        <span class="step-number">2</span>
        <div class="step-body">
          <h3 class="step-title">Review both pages</h3>
          <p class="step-desc">
            The agent opens each URL in Chrome and reads the page content via AppleScript —
            this works on most competitor sites that block traditional browser automation.
            Where possible it takes targeted screenshots of specific patterns worth calling out.
            Screenshots are saved to <code>src/assets/reports/competitors/[slug]/</code>.
          </p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="step">
        <span class="step-number">3</span>
        <div class="step-body">
          <h3 class="step-title">Section-by-section comparison</h3>
          <p class="step-desc">
            The agent divides each page into sections (above the fold, product information, social
            proof, cross-sell, etc.) and compares each section across both pages. For every section
            it asks: does the competitor do something Myprotein doesn't? Is there a meaningful
            quality difference? It looks for patterns across UX, content strategy, trust signals,
            navigation, and conversion mechanics.
          </p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="step">
        <span class="step-number">4</span>
        <div class="step-body">
          <h3 class="step-title">Opportunities are filtered for genuine gaps</h3>
          <p class="step-desc">
            The agent applies a conservative filter: it only includes an opportunity if (a) the
            competitor demonstrably does it, (b) Myprotein demonstrably doesn't or does it worse,
            and (c) it would plausibly improve conversion, usability, or trust for Myprotein's
            audience. Parity items — where both pages perform similarly — are discarded.
          </p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="step">
        <span class="step-number">5</span>
        <div class="step-body">
          <h3 class="step-title">Report is written</h3>
          <p class="step-desc">
            The agent writes <code>src/pages/reports/competitors/[slug].astro</code> using the
            <code>ReportLayout</code> wrapper. Each opportunity card shows the competitor screenshot,
            the equivalent Myprotein state, a description of the gap, and a recommended action.
            If multiple competitors were reviewed in the same run, they're grouped by opportunity
            theme rather than brand.
          </p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="step">
        <span class="step-number">6</span>
        <div class="step-body">
          <h3 class="step-title">Agent hands back to you</h3>
          <p class="step-desc">
            The agent tells you how many opportunities it found and lists the files it created.
            If it found zero genuine opportunities, it explains which sections were reviewed and
            why nothing met the threshold — that's also useful information.
          </p>
        </div>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Committing the output ──────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="guide-section">
    <h2 class="section-heading">Committing and publishing the output</h2>

    <h3 class="sub-heading">Files created</h3>
    <ul class="file-list">
      <li><code>src/pages/reports/competitors/[slug].astro</code> — the analysis report page</li>
      <li><code>src/assets/reports/competitors/[slug]/*.png</code> — competitor screenshots</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="sub-heading">Step 1 — Commit in GitHub Desktop</h3>
    <p class="guide-body">
      Open GitHub Desktop. The new report file and screenshots will appear as uncommitted
      changes in the left panel. Select all of them, write a short commit message in the
      summary field, and click <strong>Commit to main</strong>.
    </p>
    <p class="guide-body">Suggested commit message format:</p>
    <pre class="code-block">Add competitor analysis: PDP — Gymshark, Bulk, TPW (2026-06-08)</pre>

    <h3 class="sub-heading">Step 2 — Push to GitHub</h3>
    <p class="guide-body">
      Click <strong>Push origin</strong> in GitHub Desktop. This sends your commit to GitHub
      and triggers an automatic Vercel redeploy — the report is usually live within 2 minutes.
    </p>

    <h3 class="sub-heading">Step 3 — Verify the report is live</h3>
    <p class="guide-body">
      Visit <code>/reports/competitors/[slug]</code> on the deployed site to confirm the page
      is live and all competitor screenshots load correctly.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Example output ────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="guide-section">
    <h2 class="section-heading">Example output</h2>
    <p class="guide-body">
      The PDP competitor analysis from 8 June 2026 covers 6 brands — The Protein Works,
      Optimum Nutrition, Healf, Huel, Bulk, and Naked Nutrition — and surfaces 14 opportunities
      across trust signals, content, and conversion mechanics:
    </p>
    <a href="/reports/competitors/pdp-competitor-analysis-2026-06-08" class="example-link">
      View: PDP Competitor Analysis (June 2026) →
    </a>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Tips and common issues ────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="guide-section">
    <h2 class="section-heading">Tips and common issues</h2>
    <ul class="tips-list">
      <li>
        <strong>Zero findings is a valid result.</strong>
        Don't interpret an empty report as a failure. It means the competitor doesn't do anything
        on that page that Myprotein doesn't already do. That's useful to know — it tells you the
        page is competitive and your design energy should go elsewhere.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Competitor page content isn't loading.</strong>
        The Claude browser tool is blocked on most external domains. The agent uses AppleScript
        to read page content directly from Chrome instead — this works on the vast majority of
        competitor sites. If a page is behind a login or uses heavy bot detection that blocks
        even this, the agent will flag it. For those cases, describe the pattern in plain English
        and the agent can write a structured opportunity card from your description.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Only compare equivalent page types.</strong>
        A competitor's PDP compared to Myprotein's PLP won't produce useful output. Make sure both
        URLs are the same page type and, where possible, comparable product categories
        (e.g. protein powder vs protein powder, not protein vs clothing).
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Running multiple competitors in one session.</strong>
        You can pass multiple competitor URLs in one message — the agent will screenshot all of
        them and produce a single consolidated report grouped by opportunity theme. This is usually
        more useful than one report per brand.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Report includes something that Myprotein already does.</strong>
        Sometimes the agent misses a Myprotein feature on a specific page variant or test cell.
        If an opportunity is already addressed, add a note in the report file and commit — it
        keeps a historical record and you don't need to re-run the agent.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

</ReportLayout>

<style>
  .setup-callout {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 14px;
    background: #EEF6F7;
    border: 1px solid rgba(0, 57, 66, 0.18);
    border-left: 4px solid var(--color-primary);
    border-radius: 0 10px 10px 0;
    padding: 16px 20px;
    margin-bottom: 40px;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: background 0.15s;
    max-width: 680px;
  }
  .setup-callout:hover { background: #E4F0F2; }
  .setup-callout-icon { font-size: 18px; color: var(--color-primary); opacity: 0.6; flex-shrink: 0; margin-top: 1px; }
  .setup-callout-title { font-size: 14px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--color-text-heading); margin-bottom: 4px; }
  .setup-callout-sub { font-size: 13px; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--color-text-body); }

  .agent-intro { margin-bottom: 48px; }
  .agent-eyebrow {
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--color-primary);
    opacity: 0.5;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }
  .agent-h1 {
    font-size: clamp(26px, 4vw, 38px);
    font-weight: 800;
    color: var(--color-text-heading);
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    line-height: 1.15;
  }
  .agent-summary {
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-text-body);
    max-width: 680px;
  }

  .guide-section { margin-bottom: 52px; }
  .section-heading {
    font-size: 20px;
    font-weight: 800;
    color: var(--color-text-heading);
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    padding-bottom: 10px;
    border-bottom: 2px solid rgba(0,57,66,0.08);
  }
  .sub-heading {
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-text-heading);
    margin: 20px 0 8px;
  }

  .guide-body {
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--color-text-body);
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }
  .guide-body--tip {
    background: var(--color-bg-muted);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-mint);
    padding: 10px 14px;
    border-radius: 0 6px 6px 0;
    margin-top: 12px;
  }

  .checklist {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 10px;
  }
  .checklist li {
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--color-text-body);
    padding-left: 22px;
    position: relative;
  }
  .checklist li::before {
    content: '→';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--color-primary);
    opacity: 0.4;
    font-size: 13px;
  }

  .trigger-block { margin-bottom: 16px; }
  .trigger-command {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 15px;
    font-family: 'SF Mono', 'Fira Code', monospace;
    background: var(--color-primary);
    color: var(--color-mint);
    padding: 8px 18px;
    border-radius: 8px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.01em;
  }
  .trigger-examples {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 8px;
    margin-bottom: 14px;
  }
  .trigger-chip {
    font-size: 13px;
    background: var(--color-bg-muted);
    border: var(--card-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-chip);
    padding: 5px 12px;
    color: var(--color-text-body);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  code {
    font-family: 'SF Mono', 'Fira Code', monospace;
    font-size: 12.5px;
    background: var(--color-bg-muted);
    color: var(--color-primary);
    padding: 2px 6px;
    border-radius: 4px;
  }

  .code-block {
    font-family: 'SF Mono', 'Fira Code', monospace;
    font-size: 13px;
    background: var(--color-bg-muted);
    color: var(--color-text-heading);
    padding: 16px 20px;
    border-radius: 8px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    overflow-x: auto;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    border: var(--card-border);
    white-space: pre;
  }

  .file-list {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 6px;
    margin-bottom: 4px;
  }
  .file-list li {
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--color-text-body);
    padding-left: 16px;
    position: relative;
  }
  .file-list li::before {
    content: '·';
    position: absolute;
    left: 4px;
    color: var(--color-primary);
    opacity: 0.4;
  }

  .steps { list-style: none; display: flex; flex-direction: column; }
  .step {
    display: flex;
    gap: 20px;
    align-items: flex-start;
    padding: 24px 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(0,57,66,0.08);
  }
  .step:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .step-number {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 34px;
    height: 34px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--color-primary);
    color: var(--color-mint);
    font-size: 13px;
    font-weight: 800;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    margin-top: 2px;
  }
  .step-title {
    font-size: 15px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-text-heading);
    margin-bottom: 6px;
  }
  .step-desc {
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--color-text-body);
  }

  .example-link {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-primary);
    text-decoration: none;
    border: var(--card-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-card);
    padding: 14px 20px;
    background: var(--color-bg-card);
    transition: box-shadow 0.15s, transform 0.1s;
  }
  .example-link:hover {
    box-shadow: var(--card-shadow);
    transform: translateY(-1px);
  }

  .tips-list {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 16px;
  }
  .tips-list li {
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--color-text-body);
    background: var(--color-bg-card);
    border: var(--card-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-card);
    padding: 16px 18px;
  }
  .tips-list strong {
    display: block;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-text-heading);
    margin-bottom: 4px;
  }
</style>
